ex4D:plugin-description.p: This 4D plugin allows the creation of XLS documents using the xlslib 2.3.4 library.
The spreadsheet is exported in BIFF8 (Unicode) format.
iconv is included in the bundle.

ex4D:command-description.p: Create a new format object, which can apply to a cell or group of cells. You should release the reference with XLS FORMAT RELEASE when you no longer need to reference the format; otherwise, the number of references will keep increasing and take longer for the plugin to resolve.

Create a new font object, which can apply to a cell or group of cells. You should release the reference with XLS FONT RELEASE when you no longer need to reference the font; otherwise, the number of references will keep increasing and take longer for the plugin to resolve.

ex4D:argument.label: name
ex4D:argument.p: Name of the font to use.

ex4D:command-description.p: Export the workbook document to path.
Clear the workbook object from memory.
Create a new workbook. You should clear the reference with XLS WORKBOOK CLEAR when you are done.
Create a new worksheet. You should release the reference with XLS WORKSHEET RELEASE when you no longer need to reference the sheet.

ex4D:argument.label: name
ex4D:argument.p: Name for the newly created sheet.

ex4D:command-description.p: Create a new formula object. You should release the reference with XLS NODE RELEASE when you no longer need to reference the node.

Create an node specified by two cells. You should release the reference with XLS CELL RELEASE when you no longer need to reference the expression; otherwise, the number of references will keep increasing and take longer for the plugin to resolve.

Create an node specified by one cell. You should release the reference with XLS CELL RELEASE when you no longer need to reference the expression; otherwise, the number of references will keep increasing and take longer for the plugin to resolve.
Create a new formula object, which refers to another node. You should release the reference with XLS NODE RELEASE when you no longer need to reference the node.
Create a new formula object, which refers to a pair of other nodes. You should release the reference with XLS NODE RELEASE when you no longer need to reference the node.
Set the height of a row.

ex4D:argument.label: sheet
ex4D:argument.p: The position of row, starting from 0.

ex4D:argument.label: height
ex4D:argument.p: The width. Unit is one 20th of a point.

ex4D:command-description.p: Set the width of a column. Note: This command is not working for MS Excel for Mac OS X.

ex4D:argument.label: column
ex4D:argument.p: The position of column, starting from 0.

ex4D:argument.label: width
ex4D:argument.p: The width. Unit is one 256th of the width of the character 0.
